{% faqAccordion title="Leaders in Training FAQ" %}
{% faqItem
   question="How old do I have to be to participate in Leaders in Training?"
   answer="You must be between 15 and 17 years old (ages 15–17) and have a desire for a growing, personal relationship with God." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="How long is the LIT program?"
   answer="The LIT program runs in 2-week sessions alongside regular summer camp sessions. We ask that you commit to at least one full 2-week session. If you are interested in a second session, you may apply for two, but we cannot guarantee multiple placements." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="Do I get paid to be a part of Leaders in Training?"
   answer="No, LIT is a volunteer opportunity. Housing and all meals are provided for the duration of your session at camp." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="When will I find out which weeks I will be volunteering?"
   answer="Applications will be reviewed and applicants will be notified by mid-May. If accepted, you will be required to attend Staff Training Day in June." /%}
{% faqItem
   question="What does a day of Leaders in Training look like?"
   answer="Every morning before breakfast, LITs spend time in personal devotion. At each meal you sit with the campers, build relationships, and encourage positive life skills. After each meal, LITs are responsible for cleaning the dining room. Each day you will either do a work project in the morning and participate in afternoon activities with campers, or the other way around. LITs run the snack shack, participate in the evening game, and attend Chapel each night. Before bed, LITs gather together for reflection and prayer." /%}
{% /faqAccordion %}

